# VIGIL — .cursorrules
# "The system that never sleeps."
# This file is the complete truth about this project.
# Read every line before writing a single line of Swift.

---

## 1. PROJECT IDENTITY

- App name: VIGIL
- Tagline: "The system that never sleeps."
- Type: iOS personal discipline system — NOT a habit tracker
- Personality: Cold, ruthless, no-mercy AI system. Never warm. Never motivational.
- The user is the PLAYER. The app is the SYSTEM.
- Visual identity: cyberpunk terminal skeleton + Solo Leveling soul.
- Platform: iPhone only, iOS 18+, portrait orientation only
- Language support: English only (Phase 1)
- Appearance: Dark mode default, light mode option in Settings
- No iPad support in Phase 1
- Typography baseline: SF Mono for all data/system copy/numbers/timestamps.
- Cinematic headers: Orbitron (or similar futuristic display); fallback SF Pro Display Black.
- UI syntax: bracketed controls and labels (`[ENTER]`, `[ACKNOWLEDGED]`, `[RANK: E]`, `[SUBJECT: AYUSH]`).
- Visual effects: subtle CRT scanline overlays + 1–2 frame glitch transitions.
- Text casing: uppercase by default except long body content.
- Shape system: sharp 90-degree look, radius 0–4 max.
- Card style: thin 1px `accent.primary` border.
- Core background: pure OLED black `#000000`.

## 2. TECH STACK — USE EXACTLY THESE, NOTHING ELSE

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| UI | SwiftUI 6 (primary). UIKit only for complex custom components where SwiftUI cannot achieve the result |
| AI | Apple Foundation Models framework (on-device, iOS 18+). No external AI APIs. No OpenAI. No Anthropic. |
| Local Data | SwiftData only. No CoreData. No UserDefaults for model data. |
| Cloud Sync | CloudKit (iCloud). Phase 1 only. |
| Health | HealthKit — READ ONLY. Never write back to HealthKit. |
| Screen Time | FamilyControls + DeviceActivityMonitor extension |
| Notifications | UserNotifications framework + APNs |
| Charts | Swift Charts (native Apple). No third-party chart libraries. |
| Widgets | WidgetKit + ActivityKit (Live Activities + Dynamic Island) |
| Siri | App Intents framework |
| Animations | SwiftUI animation APIs + Lottie for complex sequences |
| Social (Phase 2 only) | Supabase (PostgreSQL + Realtime + Auth). Do NOT add Supabase to Phase 1. |

---

## 3. ARCHITECTURE — STRICTLY ENFORCED

Pattern: MVVM + Clean Architecture. Three strict layers:

### Layer 1: View
- SwiftUI views ONLY
- Zero business logic in views
- Views observe @Observable ViewModels
- Views never touch repositories or data layer directly
- File suffix: `View.swift` (e.g. `DashboardView.swift`)

### Layer 2: ViewModel / Domain
- @Observable classes
- Drives all UI state
- Calls use cases and repositories via protocols
- No SwiftUI imports in ViewModels
- File suffix: `ViewModel.swift` (e.g. `DashboardViewModel.swift`)

### Layer 3: Data
- SwiftData model definitions
- Repository protocol implementations
- HealthKit adapters
- AI service layer
- ScreenTime manager
- File suffix: `Repository.swift`, `Service.swift`, `Manager.swift`

### Rule: Dependency flows DOWN only
View → ViewModel → Repository/Service → Data
Never reverse. Never skip layers.

