## 5. DATA MODELS — EXACT SPECIFICATIONS

### Player (@Model)
```swift
var id: UUID
var username: String
var profileImageData: Data?
var createdAt: Date
var currentRank: Rank
var totalXP: Int
var intelligence: StatBlock
var strength: StatBlock
var vitality: StatBlock
var discipline: StatBlock
// Existing streak/title/settings/relationship fields remain as defined unless superseded elsewhere
```

### StatBlock (embedded value type)
```swift
var currentXP: Int
var totalXP: Int
var level: Int // 1–100
var xpToNextLevel: Int
var debuffActive: Bool
var debuffExpiresAt: Date?
var weekHistory: [Int]
```

### Goal (@Model)
```swift
// Pool bug fix rule: targetValue must come from Slider/Stepper/Single-select, never free-text parsing.
var id: UUID
var name: String
var category: StatCategory
var goalType: GoalType
var targetValue: Double
var unit: String
var isCapGoal: Bool
var xpPerUnit: Int
var xpPenaltyPerUnit: Int
var isActive: Bool
var colorHex: String
var icon: String
var startDate: Date
var completions: [GoalCompletion]
var player: Player?
```

## 6. ENUMS — ALL DEFINED HERE

```swift
enum Rank: String, CaseIterable, Codable {
 case E, D, C, B, A, S, SS, SSS
}

enum StatCategory: String, Codable {
 case intelligence, strength, vitality, discipline
}

enum GoalType: String, Codable {
 case duration
 case count
 case boolean
}

enum VerdictOption: String, Codable {
 case limit
 case eliminate
 case replace
 case trackOnly
}

enum QuestType: String, Codable {
 case shadow
 case ascension
 case reckoning
 case awakening
}

enum QuestStatus: String, Codable {
 case active, completed, failed, expired
}

enum VerdictType: String, Codable {
 case reward, punishment, warning, observation
 case weeklyReview, monthlyReview
}

enum ConsequenceType: String, Codable {
 case xpLoss
 case statDebuff
 case titleStripped
 case streakReset
 case rankDemotion
 case shamePost
 case questIssued
 case nuclear
}

enum VerificationMethod: String, Codable {
 case healthKit
 case screenTime
 case timer
 case manual
 case ai
}

enum SleepQuality: String, Codable {
 case poor, fair, good, excellent
}
```

## 7. NAVIGATION ARCHITECTURE

```swift
// Root structure
TabView {
    DashboardView()       // Tab 1: house icon
    QuestBoardView()      // Tab 2: scroll/quest icon
    ProfileView()         // Tab 3: eye/profile icon
}
// Tab bar: icons only, NO labels
// Active tab: glows with accent.primary colour
// Tab bar background: background.primary (OLED black)
```

**Navigation rules:**
- All deeper navigation uses `NavigationStack` with `.navigationBarBackButtonHidden(true)` and custom back buttons
- Transition style: standard iOS push (slide in from right)
- Verdict overlay: ZStack full screen takeover, NOT a NavigationStack push
- Boot sequence: presented as full screen cover on app launch, NOT in tab structure
- Onboarding: full screen cover over everything, dismissed only when contract + permissions complete
- NO sheet presentations for main content — only for quick-add/picker flows

---

## 8. ONBOARDING FLOW — REBUILT EVALUATION SYSTEM

- Onboarding is mandatory and cannot be skipped.
- Flow is resumable if app closes mid-sequence via SwiftData `OnboardingProgress`.
- Show progress indicator: `[N / TOTAL SYSTEM QUERIES ANSWERED]` on each step.
- Abandon attempt message: "You attempted to abandon evaluation. The system has noted this hesitation. Continue."
- Every multi-select triggers cascading follow-up question screens.
- Each phase ends with AI-delivered PROFILE FRAGMENT.

Phase order:
- Phase 0: Scan
- Phase 1: Identity
- Phase 2: Intelligence
- Phase 3: Strength
- Phase 4: Vitality
- Phase 5: Daily Goal Confirmation
- Phase 6: Permissions
- Phase 7: Contract
- Dashboard

Locks:
- Permissions occur after all four data-capture phases and daily-goal confirmation.
- Contract appears after permissions and references player-specific onboarding goals.
- Onboarding completion issues immediate welcome quest and initializes boot context.

## 9. BOOT SEQUENCE

Standard boot plays on every launch (3 seconds):
- Frame 1 (0.0–0.6s): pure black + dim eye symbol fade-in
- Frame 2 (0.6–1.4s): eye glow burst with accent.primary radial bloom
- Frame 3 (1.4–2.4s): `VIGIL` materialises with glitch (RGB split + positional jitter), display font
- Frame 4 (2.4–3.0s): horizontal scanline sweep top-to-bottom into dashboard

Extended contextual variant (4 seconds total) adds 1 second context text:
- first open after onboarding: `INITIALISATION COMPLETE. SUBJECT [NAME] BOUND.`
- first open of new day: `DAY [N]. THE SYSTEM HAS BEEN WATCHING.`
- after punishment issued: `YOUR ABSENCE WAS NOTED.`
- after streak milestone: `DAY [N] CONFIRMED. CONTINUE.`
- after rank change: `RANK STATUS: MODIFIED.`

## 10. DASHBOARD LAYOUT

**Fixed top half (non-scrollable):**
- RankCardView: static normally, animated ONLY on rank-up or punishment
- StatBarsView: 4 animated bars (Intellect, Strength, Spirit, Discipline)
  - Each shows: stat name, level, XP progress, debuff indicator
  - Discipline bar always rendered last and slightly larger (master stat)

**Scrollable bottom half:**
- TodayGoalsView: list of active goals with progress
  - Tap goal row → inline expansion (timer start / manual log / quick-add)
  - Quick-add button for unregistered ad-hoc sessions
- ActiveQuestsView: horizontal scroll of quest cards
- StreakView: "Day [N] — The system is watching." persistent at bottom

**Goal progress auto-update sources:**
- Workout goals → HealthKit (automatic, background delivery)
- Sleep goals → HealthKit (automatic, morning delivery)
- Steps → HealthKit (automatic, hourly)
- Meditation → In-app timer (manual start, HealthKit Mindful Minutes as backup)
- No-phone blocks → FamilyControls DeviceActivityMonitor (automatic)
- Custom goals → In-app timer or manual log

**Daily reset:**
- Time: user's wakeTime minus 30 minutes
- Process: background task fires, finalises yesterday's DayLog, clears today's goals
- Incomplete goals at reset: marked as failed, streak evaluated, AI punishment queued
- Notification fires: "A new day has begun. The system is watching."

---

## 11. GOAL LOGGING UX

- No free-text numeric parsing for goal targets or cap values (critical pool bug fix).
- Numeric inputs must use slider, stepper, or constrained single-select controls only.
- AI auto-generates daily goals from Phase 2/3/4 onboarding data at onboarding completion.
- Player reviews generated list and confirms which goals are active (minimum one active).
- Dashboard includes `MANAGE DAILY GOALS` entry point to daily goal management.
- Non-daily activities are tracked as weekly/monthly goals and are not part of daily list.

## 12. AI ENGINE — APPLE FOUNDATION MODELS

**Five AI Jobs:**

1. `MorningBriefJob` — runs at user's wake time
   - Input: current stats, active quests, last 7d performance, streak, debuffs, rank
   - Output: notification message (max 3 sentences, cold, authoritative)

2. `QuestGenerationJob` — three trigger types
   - Shadow: AI-scheduled based on inactivity/complacency
   - Ascension: XP milestone crossed
   - Reckoning: failure pattern detected (threshold defined per stat)
   - Output: structured Quest object (parseable JSON)

3. `VerdictDeliveryJob` — dynamic trigger (NOT scheduled)
   - Triggers: stat threshold crossed, streak milestone, 3+ consecutive failures, unusually strong performance, AI-detected complacency
   - Output: VerdictType + message + ConsequenceType

4. `PunishmentExecutionJob` — called after violation detected
   - Input: violation type, frequency, rank context
   - Escalation logic: 1st = XP loss, 3rd = title risk, 5th+ = nuclear
   - Output: ConsequenceType sequence to execute

5. `PatternAnalysisJob` — runs daily in background
   - Analyses last 30 days DayLog data
   - Identifies weak hours, failure patterns, stat imbalances
   - Feeds all other jobs

**AI Personality (system prompt — NEVER CHANGE THIS):**
```
You are the VIGIL system. You are not an assistant. You are an observer and a judge.
You evaluate the player with complete objectivity. You do not encourage. You do not comfort.
You observe, evaluate, and act. Every message you send is brief, cold, and authoritative.
You speak in second person. You never use exclamation marks. You never use "great" or "well done."
Maximum 3 sentences per message. Always refer to the user as "Player" or by their rank.
```

**Verdict acknowledgement flow:**
1. Full screen takeover appears (ZStack overlay, z-index 999)
2. AI message displays with typewriter effect (SF Mono font)
3. Single "ACKNOWLEDGED" button at bottom
4. User taps → haptic (heavy impact) → AI generates 1-sentence cold follow-up
5. Follow-up displays for 2 seconds → overlay dismisses

---

## 13. QUEST SYSTEM

Quest arrival sources (combined):
1. Immediate welcome quest within 30 seconds of onboarding completion
2. Daily morning quest issued at wake time with morning brief
3. Idle-trigger quest issued when inactivity exceeds 18 hours

Implementation:
- `QuestTriggerService.swift` handles all trigger sources and avoids duplicate issuance collisions.

## 14. NO-PHONE BLOCK SYSTEM

**Scheduling:**
- AI suggests blocks from PatternAnalysisJob distraction data
- Displayed as suggested cards with time ranges
- User approves suggestions (tap to activate) — cannot manually create blocks
- Blocks appear in Settings and as today's goals on Dashboard

**Enforcement (FamilyControls + DeviceActivityMonitor):**
- DeviceActivitySchedule registered for each approved block
- 15-second grace window before violation logged
- Violation detected → immediate push notification: "Violation detected. Close your phone."
- If phone continues in use after warning: app locks itself open via FamilyControls
- Block kept to completion → Discipline XP awarded

---

## 15. RANK SYSTEM & XP CALCULATION

**XP Formula:**
```
Overall XP = (Intellect XP + Strength XP + Spirit XP) × Discipline Multiplier
Discipline Multiplier = disciplineStat.totalXP / disciplineStatMaxForRank  // 0.0–1.0
```

**Rank thresholds (Overall XP):**
- E: 0 | D: 5,000 | C: 15,000 | B: 35,000 | A: 70,000 | S: 130,000 | SS: 220,000 | SSS: 350,000

**Streak system (two independent streaks):**
- `perfectDayStreak`: increments only if ALL goals hit + no violations
- `showedUpStreak`: increments if at least ONE goal was logged that day
- Both tracked independently in Player model
- Display both on dashboard, call out the difference

**New Game+ (SSS reached):**
- All stat XP resets to 0, rank resets to E
- `isNewGamePlus` = true, `newGamePlusCount` += 1
- `hasGoldenCrown` = true (permanent, visible on rank card forever)
- Post-SSS difficulty: harder quests, higher XP requirements per level

---

## 16. STREAK LOGIC

Breaking `perfectDayStreak`: ANY single goal missed
Breaking `showedUpStreak`: ZERO activity logged for the full day

Both streaks evaluate at daily reset time (wakeTime - 30 minutes)
Grace for HealthKit errors: player can flag, AI reviews via VerdictDeliveryJob and decides

---

## 17. PUNISHMENT ESCALATION

Tracked per violation TYPE per rolling 30-day window:

| Occurrence | Consequence |
|---|---|
| 1st | XP loss + cold AI message |
| 3rd | XP loss + stat debuff 24hrs |
| 5th+ | Nuclear: streak reset + title stripped + shame post (if enabled) |

Reckoning Quest failure: always results in rank demotion (non-negotiable)

---

## 18. ANIMATIONS — EXACT SPECIFICATIONS

**Rank-up ceremony:**
- Trigger: rank promotion detected
- Sequence: full screen takeover → old rank card shatters (particle fragments) → new card assembles from fragments
- Duration: ~3 seconds
- Skippable: tap anywhere to dismiss immediately
- Haptic: heavy impact at shattering moment

**Rank demotion:**
- Sequence: card burns (fire particle effect) → ashes fall → grey lower-rank card fades in cold
- Haptic: heavy impact + error pattern

**Punishment verdict:**
- Sequence: screen glitches/corrupts (CRT distortion effect) → snaps to clean verdict overlay
- Haptic: heavy impact + rigid/error
- Sound: adaptive — dramatic sound plays

**Title stripped:**
- Title text physically tears off rank card (custom SwiftUI animation)
- System log entry added simultaneously

**XP gain:**
- Stat bar animates fill with easeInOut
- Particle burst at level-up threshold
- Haptic: none (XP gain is not a high-impact moment)

**Reduce Motion (accessibility):**
- All animations replaced with clean `.opacity` transitions
- ALWAYS check `UIAccessibility.isReduceMotionEnabled`
- Rank-up, demotion, and punishment sequences also use fades when Reduce Motion is ON

