## 21. NOTIFICATIONS — ALL COPY DEFINED HERE

All notification copy lives in `NotificationContent.swift`. Never hardcode strings elsewhere.

| Type | Title | Body |
|---|---|---|
| Morning Brief | "VIGIL" | AI-generated (max 3 sentences) |
| Quest Issued | "New Assignment" | "A quest has been assigned. You have [N] hours." |
| Deadline Warning | "Clock Running" | "[Quest title]. Time is running out." |
| Block Violation | "Violation Detected" | "Discipline XP deducted. The system has noted this." |
| Daily Reset | "New Day" | "A new day has begun. The system is watching." |
| Punishment | "System Judgement" | "The system has rendered judgement." |
| Streak Milestone | "Noted" | "Day [N] complete. The system has noted this." |
| Inactivity | "Absence Noted" | "18 hours of silence. The system does not wait." |

User can toggle each type independently in Settings (NotificationManager reads these flags before scheduling)

